            "title": "NJ Mutual Funds",
            "content": "<p>NJ Mutual Fund India Invest is a major mutual fund distributor in India. SEBI awarded the company permission to launch a mutual fund in April 2021. The NJ Group includes NJ India. The NJ Group is noted for its investment management approach that is professionally managed, quality-focused, and customer-centric. To ensure convenience and value for clients, the NJ Group focuses on internal processes and technology upgrades.</p>\n<p>This group's portfolio management service (PMS) was founded in 2010 with the goal of introducing data-driven and rule-based investment methods to sophisticated clients.</p>\n<p>NJ AMC has set some of these marks in recent times in the capital market:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>NJ PMS, which is part of the NJ mutual fund company.</li>\n<li>With its experience as one of the country's largest portfolio managers, the NJ AMC believes the moment is perfect to use its investment philosophy to assist retail investors across the country with the introduction of its mutual fund.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>NJ India mutual fund hopes to deliver solutions that are differentiated and carefully developed to fulfill varied risk-return demands of investors with the debut of its mutual fund.</p>",
            "category": "null",
            "sub_category": "null"
        },
        {
            "title": "How to Invest in NJ Mutual Funds",
            "content": "<p>Exposure to diverse shares of fixed income tools is the primary benefit of investing in mutual funds. There are numerous methods to invest in NJ Mutual Fund, including</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong> Offline Method -</strong> It is the traditional technique of investing in a mutual fund that enlists the assistance of sub-brokers, agents, and advisors to assist the investor in selecting the appropriate plan. The NJ Mutual Funds portfolio could be built using an offline mutual fund application form.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The prerequisites for investing in a mutual fund scheme are as follows:</p>\n<p>- A bank account in your name with MICR and IFSC information is required.</p>\n<p>- PAN Card</p>\n<p>- KYC Compliance</p>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li><strong> Online Method - </strong>Most mutual fund firms allow you to invest in mutual funds online. You have the option of investing via NJ Mutual Funds' official portal and application. All you have to do now is follow the steps outlined below:</li>\n</ol>\n<p>- KYC documents may be utilized to finish the pro</p>\n<p>- The information submitted will be examined and validated.</p>\n<p>- After that, you can place orders and purchase funds.</p>\n<p>However, you can also invest in NJ Mutual Funds online through Groww.</p>",
